4:T9d7,BeInCrypto has been recognized as a leader in digital financial journalism, winning ‘Best Website: Economics & Finance’ at the 2025 Brazil Publisher Awards (BPA). Organized by the National Association of Publishers of Brazil (ANPB), this year’s edition embraced the theme ‘Authentic Intelligence’, bringing together media leaders from across the country to honor projects that combine editorial integrity, technological creativity, and societal contributions. BeInCrypto Brasil stood out among a competitive group of finalists, including Banco Safra, Piauí Negócios, Remessa Online, and Mercado & Consumo, earning the top honor for its dedication to delivering high-quality journalism focused on the digital economy, blockchain, and financial innovation. Sponsored Sponsored Special kudos go to Luís De Magalhães, leader of BeInCrypto’s Latin America newsroom, whose vision and leadership were central to the team’s success. Luís commented: “Latin America has become one of the most dynamic regions for crypto adoption, driven by real economic needs: inflation protection, remittances, financial inclusion. Our newsroom was built on the premise that this story deserved dedicated, professional coverage in Portuguese and Spanish. This award affirms that readers value journalism that speaks to their reality, not just translates global narratives. I’m proud of what our team has accomplished, and we’re just getting started.” The BPA 2025 was co-organized by PremiumAds and sponsored by companies including Membrana Media, Taboola, AdOpt, Seox, Viads, MGID, and Teads, leaders in digital media, content, and technology. Finalists were selected by a panel of judges with expertise in communication, technology, and business, and the process was independently audited by GMKT Market Intelligence Solutions. Since 2018, BeInCrypto has grown into a leading crypto news platform, reaching over 7 million monthly readers in 26 languages. As a proud member of the Trust Project, we deliver accurate, 